definitions.definition: The opposition to the change in flow of current in an alternating current circuit, due to inductance and capacitance ; the imaginary part of the impedance . Symbol: X .
An emotional reaction in direct contradiction to rules or regulations that threaten or eliminate specific behavioral freedoms.
